### Day 3 Weather + JWT quick tests
### Use IntelliJ HTTP Client: run requests one by one.

@host = http://localhost:8080
@context = /PaolaRestApi_war_exploded
@base = {{host}}{{context}}/api/weather

### 1) Weather search (partial city)
GET {{base}}/temperature?city=zag
Accept: application/json

###

### 2) Login (issue access + refresh tokens)
POST {{base}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "username": "paola",
  "role": "read-only"
}

###

### 3) Validate token
### Paste access token from login response:
@accessToken = PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
GET {{base}}/auth/validate?token={{accessToken}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 4) Refresh token pair
### Paste refresh token from login response:
@refreshToken = PASTE_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE
POST {{base}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###

### 5) Negative test (invalid token)
GET {{base}}/auth/validate?token=abc
Accept: application/json
